proofread NEWS -- history of user-visible changes.

This file records notable user-visible changes to proofread and
proofread-popup.  For detailed development history, see the Git log.


* Changes in proofread since 0.1.0

** proofread

---
*** New local LanguageTool backend.
The new backend sends asynchronous HTTP requests to a LanguageTool v2
server.  It supports safe UTF-16 offset conversion, configurable language
and rule selection, request timeouts, and optional management of a
session-local LanguageTool server.

LanguageTool remains an optional runtime dependency used only by
LanguageTool checkers.

---
*** New backend registry.
Backends are now registered through a backend registry.  The registry
supports lazy loading, backend-specific cache identities, and
backend-specific request cancellation.

---
*** New profile/checker configuration model.
Proofread profiles can now select an ordered set of backend checkers.
Each checker has a stable name, selects a registered backend, and may
carry backend-local options.

---
*** Package sources have been reorganized.
The proofread package sources now live under "lisp/proofread/".  The
implementation is split into "proofread.el", "proofread-llm.el", and
"proofread-languagetool.el".

The optional popup package now lives under "lisp/proofread-popup/".

---
*** Backend-private implementation details use feature namespaces.
Backend-private functions and variables now live under their feature
namespaces.  Shared callback scheduling and position conversion are
centralized in the core library.

---
*** Tests are split by backend.
Core, LLM, and LanguageTool tests are now independent suites.  Backend
test symbols are aligned with their feature namespaces.

---
*** The core library no longer loads GNU ELPA llm eagerly.
The core library does not load GNU ELPA "llm" until the LLM backend is
selected or required explicitly.


* Changes in proofread 0.1.0 (2026-07-13)

Initial release.

** proofread

---
*** Asynchronous, context-aware proofreading.
Proofread provides asynchronous, context-aware proofreading through
provider objects from the GNU ELPA "llm" package.

---
*** LLM JSON response handling.
Proofread supports provider-enforced JSON schema responses and
prompt-only JSON responses, with automatic selection based on provider
capabilities.

---
*** Automatic and explicit checks.
Proofread can check visible text automatically after idle time.  It also
provides explicit commands for checking the text at point, the active
region, the accessible buffer, or all visible ranges.

---
*** Mode-aware text selection.
Proofread can select ordinary text, comments, or docstrings with
mode-aware defaults.  It excludes URLs, email addresses, invisible text,
configured faces, and configured text properties.

---
*** Sentence-aware request chunking.
Proofread splits prose into bounded, sentence-aware requests with
configurable surrounding context.

---
*** Overlay diagnostics and navigation.
Diagnostics are displayed with overlays.  Commands are provided for
navigation, detailed descriptions, and a tabulated buffer-wide diagnostic
list.

---
*** Interactive and batch correction.
Proofread can correct individual diagnostics or scoped groups of
diagnostics.  Batch corrections are applied atomically as one undo step
and roll back on failure.

---
*** Session-local ignore records.
Proofread can ignore semantically identical diagnostics for the current
Emacs session.

---
*** Caching, concurrency, and stale-result handling.
Proofread caches diagnostics per buffer, queues requests behind a
configurable concurrency limit, rejects stale results after edits, and
preserves usable results when only part of a check fails.

---
*** Request lifecycle recording.
Proofread can record and inspect complete request lifecycles on demand,
including queued, active, completed, failed, and stale requests.

** proofread-popup

---
*** Optional Posframe frontend.
The proofread-popup package provides an optional Posframe frontend that
displays the diagnostic at point in a child frame.

---
*** Automatic integration with proofread-mode.
proofread-popup follows "proofread-mode" automatically while allowing
popup display to be disabled per buffer.

---
*** Customizable popup appearance.
Popup width, text appearance, and border appearance are customizable.


